one unique on its own way) is around 40- 45 kms from Chennai Koyumbedu Bus terminus or from Chennai Central-Egmore ralway stations. Locating this temple is easy,as we see good sign board near Kararpettai overbridge. <br><br>Here Lord is Bala Subramaniaya Swamy and hence no separate sannidhies for HIS concerts _Valli and Dheivanai.  HE is young Subramaniya Swamy bestowing HIS bountiful blessings on HIS devotees. In Sanctum HE is seen with 4 hands,2 at the back and 2 in front, with Blessing Bhava Mudra on one hand, rudhrakasha and HE took Birmah work for a while,that is this posture here.<br><br>HIS vahan -Mayil- Peacock is curved out of Green Emerald stone _Maragatha pachchai kal. Even Lord Ganapathi, Lord Annamalaiyar Linga swaroopam and Goddess Unnamalai Ammai, are all carved out of Green Emerald stones - very unique to this temple to see many Maragatha Kal deities. <br><br>There are 2 Lord Muruga sannidhies here, one is Aadhi Murugan or aadhi Moolavar - this was the originally installed Deity in sanctum, but later no body knows when or how this new Lord Balasubramaina Swam,y with 4 hands  was installed. <br><br>Another  intersting feature in this temple is, Lord Muruga is seen with HIS concert Valli hold her hand in wedding posture, this Uthsava moorthy is believed to usher in good marriage prospects for brides and grooms. On our visitng  day we witnessed 2 marriages at the temple.<br><br>A good visit for us on 12.03.2020 Thursday.</span></div></div><div class="lszDU"><button class="UikNM _G B- _S _T c G_ P0 wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span><div class="CECjK"><svg viewBox="0 0 25 24" width="20px" height="20px" class="d Vb UmNoP"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M5.188 7.521l6.836 6.837 6.837-6.837 1.06 1.06-7.366 7.368a.75.75 0 01-1.061 0L4.127 8.582l1.06-1.06z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div></div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB xUqsL mowmC KxBGd"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/Attraction_Review-g304556-d9861423-Reviews-Siruvapuri_Sri_Balamurugan_Temple-Chennai_Madras_Chennai_District_Tamil_Nadu.html#REVIEWS" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE">Review of: Siruvapuri Sri Balamurugan Temple</a></div><div class="TreSq"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written 12 March 2020</div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. It's also close to some theatres where you can see traditional Indian dance.</span></div></div><div class="lszDU"><button class="UikNM _G B- _S _T c G_ P0 wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span><div class="CECjK"><svg viewBox="0 0 25 24" width="20px" height="20px" class="d Vb UmNoP"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M5.188 7.521l6.836 6.837 6.837-6.837 1.06 1.06-7.366 7.368a.75.75 0 01-1.061 0L4.127 8.582l1.06-1.06z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div></div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB xUqsL mowmC KxBGd"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/Attraction_Review-g304556-d9806246-Reviews-Arulmigu_Sri_Muppathamman_Temple-Chennai_Madras_Chennai_District_Tamil_Nadu.html#REVIEWS" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE">Review of: Arulmigu Sri Muppathamman Temple</a></div><div class="TreSq"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written 22 January 2020</div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. 10A10 10 0 012 12 10 10 0 0112 2z" transform="translate(104 0)"></path></svg></div><div class="biGQs _P fiohW qWPrE ncFvv fOtGX"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/ShowUserReviews-g304556-d1983020-r740137407-Ubbalamadugu_Falls-Chennai_Madras_Chennai_District_Tamil_Nadu.html" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt ukgoS"><span class="yCeTE">A day trek along water stream!</span></a></div><div class="_T FKffI bmUTE"><div class="fIrGe _T bgMZj" style="-webkit-line-clamp:7;line-break:normal;cursor:pointer"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB KxBGd"><span class="yCeTE">#Unbalamadugufalls situated at the boarder of andhra and Tamilnadu, 20 kmts from Tada. This is also called Tada falls. <br>Sign boards are placed from Varadaiahpalem till forest entrance gate to Basecamp. Vehicles will be checked at main entrance and its no plastic zone however neither security nor some of the public doesn’t care. Eventually some of the places at falls are reflection of it. <br>Car entrance fee is 200 and for bike 50, minibus around 500. Individual entrance ticket is 20 rupees and some additional charges for Camera as well. <br>From forest main entrance, you are allowed to drive till base camp where parking area, restrooms and small hotel for snacks available. There is a watch tower in between to have a look at the beauty of surroundings. <br>From base camp, Trek starts along side of water stream. At starting point, there will be metal bridge to cross the water as depth will be there. After walking about 15 mins, will be reaching a check dam. Water storage upto 3 ft and this is suitable for all sort of crowd even you do not know swimming. When you move far, it may be deep, need to be cautious. Water was clear as i have travelled in the morning around 9 am, as and when it gets crowded, it gets dirty. This area is huge with lot of seating arrangements and to spend time. From there you will pass through lot of small and medium ponds along the water stream. Water is crystal clear, you can even consider for drinking. We will get to cross multiple places and you decide where to take a dip! As we move forward towards the fall, way becomes rocky and narrow. Last 100 to 200 mts of way is completely rocks, need to move from one to another, climb and so on. Hence, if you travel with elderly or kids, suggested to park your self somewhere in middle and not to go till the fall, unless they too adventurous 😊<br>Expected good water levels during monsoon, winter also better(i went in January). <br>Overall trek time is 4 hours up and down, 4.15 kmts with 138 meters elevation. <br>This place is safe and can travel with you friends, family except the washrooms facility available only at parking area/basecamp. Carry your own food or get it parcelled from Varadaiahpalem. There is a small canteen at parking area as well and I have seen a board that they do supply meals on request. <br>Transportation- prefer own (Car/Bike/Minivan ) Based on requirement. Public transportation Tada to Varadaiahpalem or Srikalahasti to Varadaiahpalem. From Varadaiahpalem appx about 13 kmts (30 mins drive due bad roads) need to hire a auto. <br>Suggestion: Please do not carry any plastic, even you do, pls bring it back. Its our responsibility to keep these places clean and save nature. Without our cooperation, it makes impossible for government to make it happen. </span></div></div><div class="lszDU"><button class="UikNM _G B- _S _T c G_ P0 wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span><div class="CECjK"><svg viewBox="0 0 25 24" width="20px" height="20px" class="d Vb UmNoP"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M5.188 7.521l6.836 6.837 6.837-6.837 1.06 1.06-7.366 7.368a.75.75 0 01-1.061 0L4.127 8.582l1.06-1.06z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div></div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB xUqsL mowmC KxBGd"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/Attraction_Review-g304556-d1983020-Reviews-Ubbalamadugu_Falls-Chennai_Madras_Chennai_District_Tamil_Nadu.html#REVIEWS" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE">Review of: Ubbalamadugu Falls</a></div><div class="TreSq"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written 20 January 2020</div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. regular visitor here</span></a></div><div class="_T FKffI bmUTE"><div class="fIrGe _T bgMZj" style="-webkit-line-clamp:7;line-break:normal;cursor:pointer"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB KxBGd"><span class="yCeTE">🛕 Kurungaleeswarar / Kuchalavapureeswarar Temple<br>Since 2015 I have become a regular visitor and a devotee of this temple. I feel nice when I visit here. <br><br>I am awestruck every time I see the work of art &amp; carvings on the stone pillars of temples. Few temples how many ever times I visit it is so mesmerizing &amp; gives a different energy and vibe. Kurungaleswarar temple is more than 1500 years old.<br><br>Description of various carvings on the temple pillars - - Images attached.<br><br>✴️ Yakshini/ #Hamsi with bow &amp; arrow flying on Hamsa/Swan.<br><br>⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣✴️ Salabhanjika/Yakshini or a celestial being holding a branch or snake. Is it a sculptor sculpting or a figure that can be seen near the feet, removing thorns, or is it a paduka?<br><br>✴️ Goddess Ganga or female deity standing on Makara or mythical creature. Has the body of an elephant &amp; head of a fish or crocodile.<br>Or the lady is nature spirit #Yakshi apsara Salabanjika.<br><br>⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣✴️ Pillar carving in temple mandapam. Ashva/ Horse, horseman hunting Cheetah.<br><br>⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣✴️ Siva &amp; Sakti sitting on Nandi &amp; Rishi Bhringi by the side. The 3 legs are not clearly visible but can only relate to this. <br><br>⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣✴️ Abandonded by royal parents, he was adopted by a couple passing by in the forest and named him Veeran. At the end of his life as a Martyr of Madurai, he is idolized and worshipped as Madurai Veeran.<br>Figurine of Veeran or Madurai Veeran. A nature or folk deity worshipped widely in Tamilnadu. Carved in the temple pillar as seen with a Vaal/ Indian Saber Sword &amp; Kombu or must be a bow/ water horn, like Viking horn or battle war horn).<br><br>* Thinking if this is an ancient carving - a jester-like carving in a temple pillar? With the Elf hat, the appearance looks as if from a Western country, maybe a foreign traveler who visited India. Jesters did exist in Indian kingdoms but they were witty scholars and advisors in King's court like Tenali Raman and Birbal.<br><br>* Carving of a Dragon emitting fire.</span></div></div><div class="lszDU"><button class="UikNM _G B- _S _T c G_ P0 wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span><div class="CECjK"><svg viewBox="0 0 25 24" width="20px" height="20px" class="d Vb UmNoP"><path fill-rule="evenodd" clip-rule="evenodd" d="M5.188 7.521l6.836 6.837 6.837-6.837 1.06 1.06-7.366 7.368a.75.75 0 01-1.061 0L4.127 8.582l1.06-1.06z"></path></svg></div></button></div></div><div></div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB xUqsL mowmC KxBGd"><a target="_blank" tabindex="0" href="/Attraction_Review-g304556-d10955701-Reviews-Sri_Kurungaleeswarar_Temple-Chennai_Madras_Chennai_District_Tamil_Nadu.html#REVIEWS" class="BMQDV _F G- wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE">Review of: Sri Kurungaleeswarar Temple</a></div><div class="TreSq"><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written 22 November 2022</div><div class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC.
